  "text": "In 1992, Kjeldsen-Kragh J and co-authors evaluated the effects of fish oil supplementation with or without NSAID in a double blind, clinical trial. The patients were randomized into 3 groups: in Group 1, corn oil for 16 weeks and naproxen for 10 weeks followed by a stepwise reduction to 0 mg/day during the following 3 weeks; in Group 2, EPA + DHA and naproxen for 16 weeks; in Group 3 EPA + DHA as Group 2 and naproxen as Group 1. At the end of the trial, patients in Group 2 had improved in duration of morning stiffness and global assessment by physician and patient [CITATION_1] .",
